By Li Zailei, southern weekend reporter

Southern weekend intern, Song Sijing

Associate Editor | Henin Ho

"The situation is more serious than we thought, " Liu told southern weekly on Jan. 30,2020.

The Guangdong medical team leader, Zhongshan, is the chief physician of the Infection Management Department of the National Sun Yat-sen University. He participated in the treatment of SARS in 2003 and is an expert in the field of infection management.

With the national support to Wuhan one after another, the materials of the designated hospitals in Wuhan have been ensured to a certain extent, and the manpower of medical personnel has been greatly strengthened, but the epidemic prevention situation is still very serious.

'The situation on the front lines of hospitals is very difficult, ' said Liu. 'beds are in short supply, equipment is behind the Times. The most prominent problem is confusion in management, which can easily lead to secondary transmission of the virus. '.

1
The pipeline to the front line is not very clear

1

###The pipeline to the front line is not very clear

Southern weekend: What are the main difficulties in front of the hospital now?

Yue Liu: to tell the truth, at present, we admit a relatively large number of patients every day. A lot of outpatients can't come in because the wards are limited. The nurses are on four-hour shifts and the doctors are on six-hour shifts, but in reality there are huge delays because there are so many patients. Even if it is a transfer, it will take as soon as February 3rd to set up the Mount Thor Hospital on February 3rd and the Mount Thor Hospital on February 5th.

The situation is a little more critical than we thought. There is also some improvement, with the support of the whole country to Wuhan, material is to a lot. But there is a problem is that the channel to the first-line medical staff is not too smooth, may be more "verbose" procedures.

For example, we only had 100 N95 masks left that day, which was enough for one day at most. For example, goggles, the entire ward only a few dozen, on the end of this shift is over, it can only be repeated cleansing (to use) . (the hospital) quickly responded, the relevant officials came to supervise, the same day sent 1,000, the next day sent 3,000.

This shows that the supplies of support from all over the country have already arrived. Once asked, they said that there are still many of these things, but who should receive them? I don't know. The channel is not clear. This kind of daily Supply Declaration, I think there may be problems.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Big Yue Liu was sorting out medical supplies. (photo / Photo of the interviewee)

Southern weekend: In addition to the lack of material flow, the hospital's medical situation?

Yue Liu: through the contact of the last few days, the entire medical process is basically straightened out. At that time we (refers to Guangdong medical team) took over 70 patients, 3 critically ill, 52 seriously ill, labor intensity is relatively large. This ward was handed over to the Guangdong medical team, and we continued without hesitation or complaint. However, if viewed from a medical professional point of view, Ward settings are more chaotic, patients and ward is chaos. It can only be sorted out under the existing technical conditions.

A large number of patients and their families are living together, free access, and now to escort the families out, the families will be very big opinion, resolutely not to go. From a professional point of view, it should be a single, single room, family members are not allowed to enter. Now it's basically three, four, six, and seven.

In the current situation, we're doing our best, to sort it out a little bit with current medical procedures, and the hardware was much worse in 2003, when SARS, but it was still managed well. I think there's still a little bit of management left. At least the door should be guarded, guarded, and no one should be allowed in or out.

The isolation ward is to be truly isolated and is now semi-open. So, the risk isn't just for treatment, it's for transmission.

Southern weekend: IS NUCLEIC ACID detection still a certain difficulty now?

Yue: The city is still in inspection. As far as we know, they're still being sent for testing. Take samples, send them back, the cycle is long, at least two days.

Guangdong in (January)19 when the whole province has been published, capable of the hospital will be launched (testing) . We do not have the qualifications of this hospital, it is a second-level hospital, now to experts, are certified, hope to have a rapid approval channels. If the basic equipment is available, we are able to carry out, and are now actively preparing and applying.

2
Fear of civil disorder

2

###Fear of civil disorder

Southern weekend: What's the main treatment now? What are the difficulties in implementing a treatment plan under current conditions?

In fact, the most important issue is oxygen supply. There is no specific drug for COVID-19 pneumonia. It is to improve the immune system, "oxygen therapy" or hormone therapy, and replenish energy and energy.

These are all big problems at the moment. For example, the simplest oxygen supply, oxygen supply, then the whole (human body function) will improve slowly, not enough oxygen will breathe difficult, and finally may be because of this cause of death. "Oxygen Therapy" is very critical, is now insufficient oxygen supply, pipeline aging, one patient to use high flow, other patients can not suck.

And then there's the question of, some patients are getting oxygen, some patients are not, and that creates a conflict as to why this patient is getting oxygen. The first consequence of this condition is that there is no guarantee of treatment and the second is that the potential risk is very high. The only thing I'm worried about right now is civil disorder, and if that happens, it's GonNa be terrible.

In my opinion, this is a very serious problem, I heard that other hospital district to beat the doctor behavior, we also have the situation of verbal threats to the doctor.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Guangdong medical team is consulting the patient. (photo / Photo of the interviewee)

Southern weekend: Apart from the immediate problems, what do you suggest for the medium and long term?

Yue Liu: the Infectious Disease Ward should be a special hospital layout, according to the requirements of the isolation ward. Even Tongji Hospital is also most of the general ward, was originally open, family members can enter. Now if there is no security, the Public Security Department can be stationed in these 8 designated hospitals?

Next, we're going to retrofit the second floor, which was too small, and we're going to have to re-isolate and expand the containment area, because the building can't be knocked off, so we're going to have to expand the cleaning area and the buffer zone. There used to be only a few clean zones and buffer zones. There should be a buffer zone between the clean area and the semi-polluted area, and a buffer zone between the semi-polluted area and the contaminated area. Wearing protective clothing is a buffer zone between the clean area and the semi-polluted area, a Hazmat suit is a buffer between the contaminated and semi-contaminated areas. Now there's no semi-contamination, so it's all connected. Isn't that risky? So that means we have to expand it, get it out of the semi-polluted zone, as close to standard as possible.
